			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">&lt;rant&gt;
<br />
Nothing like a bunch of whiny bastards to go and take a marginally useful spell that I was looking forward to into a spell that I just absolutely do not have to get. Whup-de-fucking-do.
<br />

<br />
Let's see.
<br />

<br />
Ancient: Elemental Spike. I get 420 mana. 2200 damage to pet, for a damage to mana ratio of 5.24. At the 6 minute mark, you only have 252 mana gained. The only saving grace is that this spell has almost double the duration, but you still don't get mana in very fast.
<br />

<br />
Elemental Simulcrum. I spent 50 mana to get 216 mana, so net is 166. Damage to pet is 1600, so it has a damage to mana ratio of 7.4 (gross) or 9.63 if they leave the cost on.
<br />

<br />
Elemental Siphon. I get 180 mana, and spend nothing (so note, at this moment, Siphon gets you more mana in the same time than Simulcrum does). Damage to pet is 1200, so it has a damage to mana ratio of 6.67
<br />

<br />
Know what all that means? It means that at present, Simulcrum is a fucking waste of a spell. It does more damage and doesn't provide a comparable amount of mana in return. The only thing the Spike has going for it is the duration, so that in 10 minutes, you can ALMOST cast Blade Strike again (mana cost 443, must have all mana in cost before spell can start reguardless if pres takes it to 1 mana).
<br />

<br />
Thanks again!
<br />
&lt;/rant&gt;</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
