			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The biggest point was splitting them.  If they are tied, they are mostly useless.
<br />

<br />
Prior to this change, if you wanted a rune, things were peachy, BUT, if you wanted a mana regen spell, you were out of luck, because the second you take the slightest amount of damage (yes, under 1000 is pretty slight) then your mana regen has just faded, and your pet is in for another thrashing to get it back up.
<br />

<br />
Generally speaking, you know when you'll need a rune, be it that you're about to engage a named solo, about to make a run past something you know you'll possibly take damage on (example: running through the deep to the ssra line so you can coth people from Grigor), about to engage a named on a raid that AE's, or about to hop into the arena.
<br />

<br />
In my opinion what you don't want, is unpredictability of the duration of the (in my opinion) completely unrelated effect.  If you took a slight amount of damage, party over, you need to redo your mana regen, this also made it very very annoying to keep up on raids with AE's, where your rune would constantly fall, but you'd be in NO risk of death due to healers.
<br />

<br />
You can still get the rune if you want it, and, that being said, it will be a LOT easier to spread out damage done to your pet, because you wont be "wasting mana regen" while waiting for pet to get it's health back up so you can get your mana regen buff again, since it will no longer "randomly" fade.
<br />

<br />
IMO this is a very good change, what we need to do now though, is work on the huge amounts of damage our pet is taking, and try to figure out an alternate method of "paying" for casting the spell.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=339789" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://anduran.customer.netspace.net.au/AnduranSig.jpg" border="0" /></a>
<br />

<br />
Officer of <a href="http://ponguild.webhop.net" target="_blank" class="postlink">Paradise of Nameless</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
