				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Here's an idea that I think you'll all like.
<br />

<br />
Instead of taking hp from the pet, you could do it in a *slightly* different way.  Put on a "beneficial" buff (on the pet) that lasts say.... 4 ticks?  Maybe 5? that will make pet take 200% melee damage.
<br />

<br />
If you think about it, this would stop you using it if your pet was sustaining damage: aka rampage, or straight up pet tanking, BUT you wouldn't normally use the siphons then anyways because of the negative hp component.  So it's no change on that front.
<br />

<br />
What it does change is when you're exp'n in groups, or on raids, where your pet is generally in combat 100% of the time so doesn't get the bonus out of combat regen that it needs to heal the damage back up, forcing you to either heal it yourself, or ignore it and hope it regens up before needing to take damage.
<br />

<br />
This would also solve Nilaman's problem of too many pet nukes when he wants to keep rune and mana regen up.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=339789" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://anduran.customer.netspace.net.au/AnduranSig.jpg" border="0" /></a>
<br />

