			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Nilaman wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Are you kidding me? The leading cause of pet death on raids is that I tap my pet when he is about to die. I need the mana more then he needs to eat that AE or rampage.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Well, Maybe I didn't explain my idea properly.  The idea was to make pet take 200% melee damage over the course of the "detrimental" effect.
<br />

<br />
Lets take 2 situations.  Each assuming 7K hp on pet.
<br />

<br />
1) You tap your pet on a raid or in a group when he's full.
<br />

<br />
Instantaneously, pets hp is *still* full under the proposed method, while the old method he would be down to 4800.
<br />

<br />
Assuming pet takes 2000 points worth of melee damage over the next 30 seconds.
<br />

<br />
Under the old method, this would bring pet down a *further* 2000 points, taking it to 2800.  Under the proposed method, it would take pet down to 3000.
<br />

<br />
2) You tap your pet on a raid when he's at 10% health (almost dead)
<br />

<br />
Pet is at 700hp, on a raid, you tap it under the old method, and it's corpsed.
<br />

<br />
Under the proposed method, the second you tap it, it's still 700 hp at the time your tap first goes off.
<br />

<br />
From this point onwards, if pet sustains no melee damage, it will live, and if it *does* sustain melee damage, there's still a chance it can enrage.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=339789" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://anduran.customer.netspace.net.au/AnduranSig.jpg" border="0" /></a>
<br />

<br />
Officer of <a href="http://ponguild.webhop.net" target="_blank" class="postlink">Paradise of Nameless</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
