				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Regardless of whether it went up by 1 point or 5 points, note that the damage done to the pet IS DISPROPORTIONATE to the mana reclaimed out of it. The spells get higher and higher damage to the pet for fewer and fewer gains back. Frankly, that's a downgraded spell, not an upgraded one. If you can't see that, I'm sorry</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Elemental Siphon - 1200 damage for 300 mana = 4 damage per mana
<br />
Pre latest change Ancient - 2200 damage for 700 mana = 3.14 damage per mana.
<br />

<br />
So yeah I guess I can't see why you are claiming its more damage per mana returned.
<br />

<br />
I agree the pre latest change Simulcrum spell was trash and needed changing to make it viable (drop the stupid 50mana cost for starters) but the Ancient was not the same it was an upgrade over Siphon, and a fairly decent one (relative to other Omens mana regen buffs).
<br />

<br />
Whilst it is annoying that we have to damage the pet to use the Siphon spells I think one needs to remember just why these were added to the game; a replacement for loss of Pet canni. This is probably why they damage pet as afterall you damaged the pet when using pet canni to generate mana. The principle is the same here.
<br />

<br />
I'm amazed to be honest to read that people have killed their pets using Siphon as its something I have never done. The damage done is insignificant in a group (pet rarely gets hit), solo (it regens it quick out of combat when you medding/pulling. Its only raids really where you have the issue and then only if the mob has a damaging AE and you need to recast it (increasing duration will drop the times you need to recast). The extra damage also means nothing if 1 shot of calliav absorbs it and calliav is commonly used on raids against mobs with damaging AE's.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=342751" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kirium</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.cestusdei.org" target="_blank" class="postlink">Cestus Dei</a>
<br />
Veeshan</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
